This paper deals with metalearning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on the average ranking method and its ability to handle incomplete metadata. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as these sub-categories are closely related to the topic of the paper. The sub-categories cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) are less likely but still possible as they may also involve metalearning and algorithm optimization.
